<text xml:lang="ta">
  <body>
    <div xml:id="PN225">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>talaiyōr nuṅkiṉ ṟīñcēṟu micaiya</l>
<l>viṭaiyōr paḻattiṉ paiṅkaṉi māntak</l>
<l>kaṭaiyōr viṭuvāyp piciroṭu cuṭukiḻaṅku nukara</l>
<l>nilamalar vaiyattu valamuṟai vaḷaii</l>
<l>vēntupī ṭaḻitta vēntuvēṟ tāṉaiyō</l>
<l>ṭāṟṟa leṉpataṉ ṟōṟṟaṅ kēḷiṉik</l>
<l>kaḷḷi pōkiya kaḷariyam paṟantalai</l>
<l>muḷḷuṭai viyaṉkāṭ ṭatuvē naṉṟuñ</l>
<l>cēṭceṉṉi nalaṅkiḷḷi kēṭkuvaṉ kolleṉa</l>
<l>viṉṉicai paṟaiyoṭu veṉṟi nuvalat</l>
<l>tūkkaṇaṅ kurīit tūṅkukū ṭēyppa</l>
<l>voruciṟai koḷīiya tirivāy valampuri</l>
<l>ñālaṅ kāvalar kaṭaittalaik</l>
<l>kālai tōṉṟiṉu nōkō yāṉē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>Listen now about [the fate of] the appearance of what is called ‘capability’, (6)</l>
<l>with an army of eminent spears that destroyed the greatness of kings (5)</l>
<l>after encircling in the order of victory the world where the ground blooms, (4)</l>
<l>while the those at the head ate the sweet slush of palmyra fruit, (1)</l>
<l>those in the middle fed on sweet ripe fruit, (2)</l>
<l>[and] the those at the end enjoyed roasted roots with a sprinkling of ???. (3)</l>
<l>[Now] it is in the thorny vast wilderness, (8a-c)</l>
<l>on saline  burial ground where spurge grew long. (7)</l>
<l>Thinking “will Cēṭceṉṉi Nalaṅkiḷḷi well listen [now]?”, (8d-9) </l>
<l>while they talk of [his] victory along with the Paṟai drum with pleasing sound, (10)</l>
<l>and when the morning appears (14ab)</l>
<l>at the gate of the world’s guardian (13)</l>
<l>with a right-spiralling conch with twisted mouth that took one side, (12)</l>
<l>so that it resembles the hanging nest of the weaver bird, (11)</l>
<l>	ah, I ache. (14cd)</l>
</lg>
    </div>
